      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i already talked to a friend who's been on it forever and she says she just takes a handful of garlic capsules every morning and feels totally fine. my doctor is kind of old school and just tells me the same thing every time. if i were to try and taper off the warfarin slowly while i start the garlic and the green smoothies, do you think that would be a safer way to transition to a natural routine? i just want a way to do this without the constant lab work.",
